revision.text:
{{notability|date=December 2017}}
'''Alan T. Davies''' (born 1933) is an [[Professor#Retired faculty|emeritus professor]] of [[religion]] at the [[University of Toronto]], Canada.<ref>[http://torontomulticulturalcalendar.com/index.php?cD=2011-04-26 Toronto MultiCultural Calendar]</ref><ref>[http://mqup.mcgill.ca/book.php?bookid=661 The Holocaust, Israel, and Canadian Protestant Churches], McGill-Queen's University Press</ref> He is also an [[Ordination|ordained]] [[Minister (Christianity)|minister]] in the [[United Church of Canada]].<ref>[http://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/antisemitism-in-canada-alan-t-davies/1100323185 Antisemitism in Canada: History and Interpretation: Meet the author], Barnes&Noble</ref>

From 1969 to 1989, Davies was lecturer and then associate professor in the Religious Studies department at [[Victoria University, Toronto|Victoria College]]. From 1989 to 1998, he was professor at the Centre for the Study of Religion of the University of Toronto. Davies conducted research into the relations between Jews and Christians.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://library.vicu.utoronto.ca/archives/holdings/f2131_allan_t_davies/ |title=Alan T. Davies fonds |work=University of Toronto archives}}</ref>

His books ''Anti-Semitism in Canada''<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=JK1pNISPmyYC&pg=PA126 |title=The Crucified Nation: A Motif in Modern Nationalism |page=126 |year=2010 |ISBN=1845194462 |last=Davies |first=Alan}}</ref> and ''How Silent Were the Churches?'' (with Marilyn F. Nefsky) received [[Canadian Jewish Book Awards]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wlupress.wlu.ca/Catalog/davies_nefsky.shtml |title=How Silent Were the Churches? |publisher=Wilfrid Laurier University Press}}</ref>

