{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}} {{Use British English|date=December 2016}} '''Spoofer McGraw''' was a British comic strip, drawn by [[Gordon Bell (artist)|Gordon Bell]], which ran in the British comics magazines [[Sparky (comic)|Sparky]] and [[The Topper (comics)|The Topper]] from 1968 to 1974.
==Concept==
Spoofer McGraw is a young boy who, as his name implies, enjoys playing spoofs and pranks on others. He would tell lengthy and completely made up explanations to answer questions sent in by readers of the magazine. His [[sidekick]], Bo, was a young boy who played the [[straight man (stock character)|straight man]] to his outlandish comments.
