{{Infobox Museum |name = War Childhood Museum |image = War_Childhood_Museum.jpg |caption = |map_type = |coordinates = {{Coord|43|51|42|N|18|25|42|E|region:BH_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} |established = 2017 |dissolved = |location = Logavina 32, [[Sarajevo]] |type = [[History museum]] |visitors = |founder = Jasminko Halilovic |publictransit = |website = [http://museum.warchildhood.com/ WCM] }}
The '''War Childhood Museum''' ([[Bosnian language|Bosnian]]: ''Muzej ratnog djetinjstva'') is a historical museum in [[Sarajevo]], [[Bosnia-Herzegovina]] that opened in January 2017. The museum presents the experiences of children who lived through the [[war in Bosnia]], told through objects, video testimonies, and excerpts from oral histories. The 2018 Council of Europe Museum Prize – one of the most prestigious awards in the museum industry – has been awarded to the War Childhood Museum as part of the European Museum of the Year Awards.<ref>{{cite news|title=Council of Europe Museum Prize 2018|url=https://europeanforum.museum/winners/council-europe/|accessdate=17 May 2018|work=European Museum Forum}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=War Childhood Museum, Sarajevo, wins 2018 Museum Prize|url=http://www.assembly.coe.int/nw/xml/News/News-View-EN.asp?newsid=6891&lang=2&cat=|accessdate=17 May 2018|work=European Museum Forum|date=January 2018}}</ref>
The project began in 2010 when Jasminko Halilovic, a Sarajevan entrepreneur, activist, and “war child,” used an online platform to collect short recollections of young adults who had been children during the Bosnian war. Over 1,000 young adults submitted their memories. Halilovic assembled these recollections into a book which was published in 2013. The book has subsequently been translated into German and Japanese.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sheehan|first1=Dan|title=Jasminko Halilovic: Children of War|url=https://www.guernicamag.com/children-of-war/|accessdate=5 February 2017|work=Guernica Magazine|date=December 2015}}</ref>
As Halilovic began corresponding with the young adults who submitted memories, he realized that many of the former “war children” still had specific objects that they connected with their memories.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Toe|first1=Rodolfo|title=Sarajevo Museum to Preserve Wartime Childhood Memories|url=http://www.balkaninsight.com/en/article/bosnian-museum-preserves-war-childhood-memories-05-11-2016|work=Balkan Transitional Justice|agency=Balkan Insight|date=May 11, 2016}}</ref> He began working with a team of other young professionals to develop a museum collection, eventually collecting over 3,000 objects and over 60 oral history testimonies.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rose|first1=Eleanor|title=Bosnia's War Childhood Museum Finally Opens|url=http://www.balkaninsight.com/en/article/bosnia-s-war-childhood-museum-finally-opens-01-30-2017|accessdate=5 February 2017|work=Balkan Transitional Justice|agency=Balkan Insight|date=January 1, 2017}}</ref>
In May 2016, the War Childhood Museum held its first, temporary exhibition at the [[Historical Museum of Bosnia and Herzegovina]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Toe|first1=Rodolfo|title=Sarajevo Museum to Preserve Wartime Childhood Memories|url=http://www.balkaninsight.com/en/article/bosnian-museum-preserves-war-childhood-memories-05-11-2016|accessdate=5 February 2017|work=Balkan Transitional Justice|agency=Balkan Insight}}</ref> Further exhibitions followed in the cities of Zenica and Visoko.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Ruvic|first1=Dado|title=Bosnian museum of wartime childhood helps heal trauma|url=http://in.reuters.com/article/bosnia-museum-idINKCN0ZO0ZV|accessdate=5 February 2017|agency=Reuters|date=July 8, 2016}}</ref> In January 2017, the museum’s permanent exhibition opened on Logavina Street in Sarajevo.
The museum’s collections feature diaries, toys, photographs, items of clothing, and a variety of other objects donated by war survivors.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Halilovic|first1=Jasminko|url=http://museum.warchildhood.com/|website=War Childhood Museum}}</ref> All the items are presented alongside first-person recollections from the individual who donated them. In addition to the items, visitors can listen to testimonies and read snippets from oral history interviews.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rose|first1=Eleanor|title=Bosnia's War Childhood Museum Finally Opens|url=http://www.balkaninsight.com/en/article/bosnia-s-war-childhood-museum-finally-opens-01-30-2017|accessdate=5 February 2017|work=Balkan Transitional Justice|date=January 30, 2017}}</ref>
